<doc id="483051" wikidata="Q2750992" url="?curid=483051" title="Pistolet-pulemet">
<text>Pistolet-pulemet (Пистоле́т-пулемёт) means submachine gun in Russian. The name is most often used in relation to a series of weapons made by the Soviet Union which includes PPD-40, PPSh-41 and PPS-43. The letter after the PP (ПП) in the gun&#x27;s designation is from the designer&#x27;s name. For example, the &quot;Sh&quot; in PPSh stands for &quot;Shpagin&quot; (Russian: &quot;Шпагин&quot;).

This name is also used in submachine guns manufactured in Russian Federation. For example, PP-19 Bizon, PP-93 and PP-2000.
